Your computer talks to other computers through ports. A port is just a numbered door like apartment numbers in a building. Different services live behind different doors
  This is a very simple port scanner using python, the basic main idea of what this program does is that it checks ports from 1 to 1024.
  - It goes from each port one by one 
  - Checks for half a second then moves on
  - The program always closes the ports before moving on using sock.close
